column5: Up here right now, weather has been very good, nice winds, partly cloudy, darn near 70 degrees. Fishing for Walleyes and Smallmouth has been excellent. Jig and crawler seems best, but minnows and leeches work too.Wind blown points working for us. Hate to leave tomorrow. JJ
Glad you've had a great time fishing. Where is the Bigstone Bay area and what camp are you fishing out off. Thanks Joe
